  <brief_title>Effect of Quality Improvement Tools in Congestive Heart Failure (CHF)</brief_title>
  <official_title>Decreased Readmissions and Improved Quality of Care With Use of Inexpensive Checklist in Heart Failure</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>St. Joseph Mercy Oakland Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>St. Joseph Mercy Oakland Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis: Quality Improvement tools like &quot;Heart Failure Discharge Checklist&quot; which
      emphasizes on proper education to patients, ensure appropriate dose titration and counselling
      improve outcome in congestive heart failure (CHF).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
